The cinders [G7]from his freight scarred his [C]face you know
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
He [F]knew every rail he knew [C]every tie
He [F]knew every water tank [C]that he passed [G7]by
And every[C]where he went they called him poor hobo
He lived a [G7]lonesome life his name was [C]Lonesome Joe
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
He knew every house and he knew every door
Where they would [G7]give a hand to a [C]poor hobo
He would tip his hat in the nicest way
